full_text:
I wondered if it was something weird like that, because the voice was constant even though the sweep was clicking away.  There were four of us in the car listening to it, and none of us could understand a word of it.  Of course no tape recorder running in the car, so no chance to go back and listen again.  The responses did seem to directly correlate to the questions we asked, e.g. the Russian stuff came right after we asked a question, and if we didn&#39;t ask a question, it was silent and we got normal radio snippets.  Really interesting.  Too bad the location where we were driving is two hours away, or I&#39;d be back there, trying it again to see if I could duplicate the happening.

Yes, I think it&#39;s crazy to say we know who these entities are.  I think it&#39;s safe to say that many or most are either dead people, or entities pretending to be dead people, but who really knows?  I just know that something is there.



